This is a blackjack game{nl}
played one-on-one{nl}
against the dealer.{waitkey}{clearbox}The computer{nl}
acts as the dealer.{waitkey}{clearbox}At the start, both the{nl}
player and dealer are{nl}
each dealt 2 cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}One of the dealer's{nl}
two cards is{nl}
face-down.{waitkey}{clearbox}Only when the dealer's{nl}
face-up card is an Ace{nl}
can you take INSURANCE.{waitkey}{clearbox}INSURANCE is explained{nl}
toward the end of{nl}
these rules.{waitkey}{clearbox}First, the player looks{nl}
at the dealer's cards{nl}
and their own to decide{nl}
whether to draw another.{waitkey}{clearbox}Choose HIT to draw{nl}
another card, or STAND{nl}
to stop.{waitkey}{clearbox}You may draw up to{nl}
7 cards as long as{nl}
your total doesn't{nl}
exceed 21.{waitkey}{clearbox}You will automatically{nl}
STAND in these cases:{waitkey}{clearbox}· Your first 2 cards{nl}
  are a Blackjack.{waitkey}{clearbox}· Your total reached{nl}
  exactly 21 from{nl}
  the 3rd card onward.{waitkey}{clearbox}· You drew 7 cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}· Your total exceeded{nl}
  21 (bust).{waitkey}{clearbox}Cards 2-10 count at{nl}
face value.{waitkey}{nl}
J through K count{nl}
as 10.{waitkey}{nl}
An Ace counts as{nl}
either 1 or 11.{waitkey}{clearbox}After the player STANDs,{nl}
the dealer draws cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}The player wins if their{nl}
total stays at or under 21{nl}
and exceeds the dealer's,{waitkey}{nl}
or if the dealer busts.{waitkey}{clearbox}If both totals are equal,{nl}
or both have Blackjack,{nl}
it is a push and{waitkey}{nl}
your bet is returned.{waitkey}{clearbox}In addition to HIT and{nl}
STAND, the player may{nl}
also use D. DOWN{nl}
and SPLIT.{waitkey}{clearbox}   <D. DOWN>   (Double Down)                  {waitkey}{clearbox}Available only when{nl}
the player holds{nl}
exactly 2 cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}The player agrees to take{nl}
exactly one more card in{nl}
exchange for doubling{nl}
their bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}Not available if your{nl}
coin total is less{nl}
than your current bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}Winning with DOUBLE DOWN{nl}
pays out at{nl}
double the normal rate.{waitkey}{clearbox}    <SPLIT>    (Split)                  {waitkey}{clearbox}Available when your{nl}
first two cards are{nl}
of equal value.{waitkey}{clearbox}Split the two cards into{nl}
two separate hands{nl}
and play each one.{waitkey}{clearbox}Not available if your{nl}
coin total is less{nl}
than your current bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}You may also D. DOWN{nl}
on each hand after{nl}
a SPLIT.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: after a SPLIT,{nl}
an Ace combined with{nl}
a 10-through-K will{waitkey}{nl}
count as 21,{nl}
not Blackjack.{waitkey}{clearbox}{nl}
[About INSURANCE]{waitkey}{clearbox}INSURANCE is a kind{nl}
of side bet offered only{nl}
when the dealer's first{nl}
card is an Ace.{waitkey}{clearbox}Choose YES to take{nl}
insurance, or NO{nl}
to decline.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you choose NO,{nl}
the game continues{nl}
normally.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you choose YES,{nl}
you first pay a premium{nl}
equal to half your bet.{waitkey}{nl}
Then, if the dealer's{nl}
other card is 10 through K,{waitkey}{nl}
meaning the dealer{nl}
has Blackjack,{nl}
your bet is forfeited,{waitkey}{nl}
but you receive 3 times{nl}
your premium and{nl}
the game ends.{waitkey}{clearbox}If the dealer's other card{nl}
is Ace through 9,{nl}
your premium is forfeited{waitkey}{nl}
and the game{nl}
continues normally.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: this game uses{nl}
4 decks (208 cards), so{nl}
the same card may{nl}
appear more than once.{waitkey}{ret}

