The numbers 1 through 9{nl}
are placed randomly in{nl}
a 3x3 grid of 9 squares.{waitkey}{clearbox}Guess the arrangement{nl}
of those numbers.{waitkey}{clearbox}The faster you solve it,{nl}
the better the prize{nl}
you receive.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you can't answer within{nl}
the set number of tries,{nl}
it's game over.{waitkey}{clearbox}The set number of tries{nl}
equals the number of{nl}
RESULT slots shown on{nl}
the right side of screen.{waitkey}{clearbox}When your answer is wrong,{nl}
the result is recorded{nl}
in the RESULT slots{nl}
in order,{waitkey}{nl}
so use them as reference{nl}
for your next attempt.{waitkey}{clearbox}Above the input area, the{nl}
CHOSEN display shows{nl}
which numbers are{nl}
selected (lit){waitkey}and which are not (unlit).{nl}
Use it to verify that{nl}
the numbers 1-9 each{nl}
appear exactly once.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: this game uses{nl}
Metal Cards instead{nl}
of coins.{waitkey}{ret}

